latestIgtvVideos.title: My Amazing Greys!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Grey hair is something that has grown over me, literally and metaphorically. Its not just a part of my physicality today but also a part of my psyche! It started as a trial - I was fed up of coloring my hair, root touch up, sitting in  parlors for hours, pour chemicals on my head, and that smell - but quickly it became a choice. After a few cycles the greys took over and i loved it, I loved the way my hair looked but I loved more the way I felt and continue to feel! I feel healthier, natural and chemical free! In grey I found lot more comfort and a sense of calm. With grey came a lot more acceptance of self and others, lot more grey cells too you see 😅
.
.
Also grey hair is equal to aging and needs more care and attention. Just as the body requires care with years so does the hair! Grey hair is a different ball game, it gets frizzy, delicate and sensitive. The melanin production reduces which protects the hair from UV rays and insulates it from heat and damage of chemicals and pollution. There are other things like loss of lipids, sebum slow down, hormonal changes etc. Grey hair care routine needs to be different, and not coloring alone does not mean goodbye to harsh chemicals. That's when @amazinggreys.in came along with a solution specially formulated for grey hair. It's vegan, cruelty free, has natural actives and is dermatologically tested. I have been using it over 6 weeks and my hair is all happy shiny! Give it a try if you are looking for grey hair care solution. Use my code APARNARAO and also get a 10% discount on your orders.

(Kabir, folk music of india, oral tradition)

The air at Courtyard Koota was charged with spiritual resonance and musical brilliance as Padmashri Prahlad Singh Tipanya and his ensemble took the stage for an unforgettable evening of Kabir bhajans. 

It was more than a concert—it was a pilgrimage through song, a reminder of what truly matters in a world often consumed by distractions.

A compilation with more moments beautifully captured by  @lightwedsshadow and @rramakanth will follow soon.

The evening at @sabhablr with Prahladji, his team and more than 200 of us was a gathering to soak in Kabir Vaani. 

Thank you all for coming. 
It was such an honour to receive all those who gathered and to listen together. 
Sabha offered the right vessel for all of us to go deeper. The space, the people, the lights, the sound, the songs, the flames the flowers everything came together for us lovingly. 
The event would not have been possible without @ektas_gatherings . 
Sharing these here now as we continue our journey this week with @prahladsinghtipanyaofficial with a 3 day workshop that begins today and a sold out concert at @courtyard_koota on 22nd. 

Bangalore you are wonderful

Who needs trends when your culture is your ultimate guide!

Style needn't be a rigid formula—it should be a fluid expression of who we are, evolving with time and need. The beauty of style lies in its adaptability, functionality, allowing us to mix the old with the new, the classic with the contemporary, and the structured with the effortless. Fluidity in style means embracing change, honoring comfort, and making room for creativity. It’s not about fitting into a box; it’s flowing freely.

And I don't see a bigger style icon than the saree!
Only an adaptive and progressive garment like this can stand the test of time and it has ❤️
She's the GOAT!

(Saree, styling tips, sari drape, culture, unstitched garment, fluid fashion, personal style, indian textiles, sustainable fashion)

There you have it!
When the scholar herself says "don't follow the scholar!" @malvika.seminar 🙏🙏

Do your thing ladies!
It's an unstitched piece piece of cloth 😍

This fluid piece of cloth deeply rooted in history, has taken different shapes and forms since ages adapting itself to climate, geography, purpose/ vocation. The saree is worn in over hundred different ways, short and long, high and low, across the length and breadth of our country and continues to evolve.

The Saree is a versatile, living, breathing, progressive - i will dare say futuristic, garment carrying within its folds history, memories, stories and the essence of this country's rich and diverse identity.

And i love it to bits ❤️

Thank you @barkha.dutt & @themojostory for this!
